<div class="quotetitle">majorspawn wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />what i am asking is i use a Ba3m board for a lorom game will the process work when wired the same as per wiring in mmonkeys guide?<br />same wiring procedure, lorom board, lo rom game<br /></div><br /><br />I haven't read the Mmonkey wiring and such, but there's no reason why it wouldn't work.... especially if your game is less than 2mbytes and uses 64k sram.  Just like chrono trigger, if all the addresses are connected properly -- whether it's by a tsop rom or dip rom -- a Lo rom game should work on a Lo rom cart.  If you burn your rom wrong or connect the wiring wrong, then it will not work.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5779">Markfrizb</a> — Fri Aug 11, 2017 10:02 pm</p><hr />
